<div id="pfe" class="pf w1 h8" data-page-no="e"><div class="pc pce w1 h8"><div class="t m1b8 x48 h21 y1d3 ff3 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I</div><div class="t m1b9 x5 h22 y1d4 ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Adult Lesson </div><div class="t m6 x33 h22 y1d5 ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1ba x3 h16 y1d6 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Tragedy an the </div><div class="t m1bb x33 h16 y1d7 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Promised Land </div><div class="t m1a8 x1f hd y1d8 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THIS WEEK&apos;S STUDY: Ruth 1:1-18. </div><div class="t m100 x31 hd y1d9 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT: &quot;And Ruth said, Intreat me not to leave thee, </div><div class="t m12f x31 hd y1da ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">or to return from following after thee: for whither thou goest, I </div><div class="t m1bc x31 hd y1db ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">will go; and where thou lodgest, I will lodge: thy people will be my </div><div class="t m1bd x31 hd y1dc ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">people, and thy God my God&quot; (Ruth 1:16). </div><div class="t m1be x1f hd y1dd ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">CENTRAL THOUGHT: </div><div class="t m1bf x28 h17 y1de ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Even when struggling in the midst of tragedy and </div><div class="t m1c0 x1f h17 y1df ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">disaster, the lives of God&apos;s people demonstrate something that captivates </div><div class="t m1c1 x1f h17 y1e0 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">those around them. </div><div class="t m1c2 x52 hd y1e1 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">OVERVIEW: Ruth 1:1-18 </div><div class="t mc4 x53 hd y1e2 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1:1-5 </div><div class="t m166 x2a hd y1e3 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Famine in Judah </div><div class="t m18e x54 hd y1e4 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1:6-10 </div><div class="t m1c3 x55 hd y1e3 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Decision to Return </div><div class="t m1c4 x50 hd y1e5 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to Bethlehem </div><div class="t m113 x4c hd y1e4 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1:11-18 </div><div class="t m131 x56 hd y1e6 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Decisions of the </div><div class="t m1c5 x57 hd y1e7 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Daughters-in-law </div><div class="t m11e x3a h17 y1e8 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Flight to Moab </div><div class="t me2 x1c h17 y1e9 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(1, 2) </div><div class="t m1c6 x5 h17 y1ea ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Elimelech dies and </div><div class="t m10b x20 h17 y1eb ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sons marry (3, 4) </div><div class="t m1c7 x1a h17 y1c ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sons die (5) </div><div class="t m1c8 xd h17 y1ec ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Naomi hears that God </div><div class="t m1c9 x58 h17 ya8 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">aids His people (6) </div><div class="t m1ca x24 h17 y64 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Naomi begins return (7) </div><div class="t m12e xd h17 y1ed ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Naomi urges Ruth and </div><div class="t m1cb x55 h17 y1c ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Orpah to stay (8, 9) </div><div class="t m64 x28 h17 yaa ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">They vow to go with </div><div class="t m1cc x59 h17 y1ee ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">her (10) </div><div class="t m1cd x57 h17 y1ef ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Naomi again urges </div><div class="t m1ce x5a h17 y1f0 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">them to return </div><div class="t m7a x4c h17 y1f1 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(11-13) </div><div class="t m1cf x56 h17 ya9 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Orpah&apos;s decision </div><div class="t m1d0 x5b h17 y1f2 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(14) </div><div class="t m1d1 x18 h17 y1f3 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ruth&apos;s decision </div><div class="t m7a x4c h17 y1f4 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(15-18) </div><div class="t mb2 x48 hd y1f5 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">INTRODUCTION: </div><div class="t m1d2 x22 h17 y1f5 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">People often dismiss the book of Ruth as little more </div><div class="t m151 x48 h17 y1f6 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">than a beautiful human love story. Some regard it as a source of types and </div><div class="t m1d3 x48 h17 y1f7 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">object lessons. But it is much more than these. It is a story of God in ac-</div><div class="t m1d4 x48 h17 y1f8 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tion—both on the human level and on the level of the great controversy </div><div class="t m1c1 x48 h17 y25 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">between good and evil. </div><div class="t m1d5 x2a h17 y1f9 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">But how can the book be about God when, except for a few passing </div><div class="t m1d6 x48 h17 y1fa ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">references to His name, He does not appear in it? Actually He does—</div><div class="t m127 x48 h17 y1fb ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through the people the story is about. &quot;The single most characteristic way in </div><div class="t m1d7 x48 h17 y1fc ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">which the story-teller makes God manifest . . . is by working out a corre-</div><div class="t m1d8 x48 h17 y1fd ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">spondence between the way God acts and the way the people in the story </div><div class="t m1d9 x48 h17 y1fe ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">act.&quot; </div><div class="t m1da x5 h17 y1ff ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;God is present and active in the Ruth story especially in the way in </div><div class="t m1db x48 h17 y200 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">which the people behave toward one another.&quot;—Edward E Campbell, Jr., </div><div class="t m1dc x48 h17 y201 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ruth, </div><div class="t m1dd x6 h17 y201 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 29. </div><div class="t m130 x5 h17 y202 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God&apos;s true followers will treat each other the way that He treats them. </div><div class="t ma9 x48 h17 y203 ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Each one of us is to be His agent, His hands and feet, as well as His voice on </div><div class="t m1de x48 h23 y204 ff2 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">14 </div><div class="t m45 x3 h23 y205 ff2 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SAB </div><div class="t m1df x43 h24 ybd ff7 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">PM </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000